Zloty Slides for Third Day Versus Euro on Greek Default Concern

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-09-12T08:10:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/zloty-slides-for-third-day-versus-euro-on-greek-default-concern.html
The Polish zloty dropped against
the euro, depreciating for a third day amid speculation  Germany 
is preparing for a Greek default.  The zloty lost 0.2 percent to 4.3066 per euro as of 10:02
a.m. in Warsaw. The currency lost 2.3 percent in a three-day
slump, headed for the steepest loss since Aug. 10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  